.TH DICTEE-RESET "1" "April 2026" "dictee 1.3.0"
.SH NAME
dictee-reset \- reset dictee system state and restart daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictee-reset
[\fISERVICE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Stop all dictee processes, clean up state files, and restart the configured ASR daemon.
Useful when the system is in an inconsistent state after a crash or hang.
.PP
If \fISERVICE\fR is specified, restart that specific service instead of the one
configured in \fI~/.config/dictee.conf\fR.
.SH ACTIONS
.TP
Stops all ASR daemons (dictee, dictee-vosk, dictee-whisper, dictee-canary)
.TP
Kills any running transcription or recording processes
.TP
Clears state files in /dev/shm/ and /tmp/
.TP
Restarts the configured daemon
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /dev/shm/.dictee_state
Runtime state file
.TP
.I ~/.config/dictee.conf
User configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dictee (1),
.BR dictee-switch-backend (1)
